<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-573-758  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 573 758.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Electronic News  June 18 1990 v36 n1814 p36(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>National terminates Nu Horizons. (National Semiconductor splitswith East Coast regional distributor)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Ferguson, Bob.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>National Semiconductor has ended its relationship with East Coastregional distributor Nu Horizons, following the latter's signingof an all-locations franchise agreement with Toshiba.andP;  Nu Horizonshad reportedly pushed National to expand the distributor'sgeographic area outside of New York and New Jersey, to no avail.andO;As National is disinclined to share distributors' shelves withforeign competitors, the Toshiba agreement may have been the laststraw that wrecked the previous agreement.andP;  Nu Horizons expects aloss of sales during fiscal year 1990 due to its split withNational, since that relationship had contributed to 22 percent ofits sales last year.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   National Semiconductor Corp. (contracts)Nu Horizons Electronics Corp. (contracts).andO;Ticker:    NSM; NUH.andO;Topic:     Distribution AgreementsFranchiseSemiconductors.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>